OL,3,CHousehold energy bills to rise #94
OL,4,Cfrom January amid record consumer debt
OL,6,FHousehold energy bills will rise on
OL,7,Faverage by #94 from January 1 after
OL,8,FOfgem increased its price cap in
OL,9,Fresponse to rising wholesale prices.
OL,11,FThe regulator's price cap is rising by
OL,12,F5% from the current #1,834 for a
OL,13,Ftypical dual fuel household to #1,928
OL,14,Ffrom Monday, driven almost entirely by
OL,15,Frising costs in the international
OL,16,Fwholesale energy market because of
OL,17,Fmarket instability and global events -
OL,18,Fparticularly the conflict in Ukraine.
